    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "12556d34_77265c11",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/multisite/consumer/AbstractSubcriber.java",
        "patchSetId": 64
      },
      "lineNbr": 125,
      "author": {
        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-16T17:10:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we might be acking too eagerly here.\n\n`broker.send()` is asynchronous, but `RequeueEventAction` returns `void`, so we acknowledge the original but we don\u0027t know whether the new copy was published successfully and ff the publish fails, the event is lost.\n\nShould we not expose the `requeue` result and only acknowledge the original after it succeeds?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 124,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 125,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a9b131b5_65c39e09",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/multisite/consumer/MultiSiteConsumerRunner.java",
        "patchSetId": 64
      },
      "lineNbr": 85,
      "author": {
        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-16T17:10:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Publishing a new copy here and breaking the ordering of the events seems wrong to me.\n\nIf the partition contains:\n```\nDELETE(A) → INDEX(A)\n```\n\nand `DELETE(A)` returns `RETRY`, we republish it at the end and acknowledge the original. The partition then become:\n\n```\nINDEX(A) → DELETE(A)\n```\n\nSo the newer index may succeed first, followed by the older delete, leaving the final index state wrong.\n\nCan we discuss about this?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 85,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 85,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "428c6319870ee9443741d9430aa4cf54b5297def",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
